## Development cycle

1. Before writing any code, come up with an extremely good plan, review the plan, and then ask the user for permission to execute the plan.
2. After you have executed the plan, run: `npx turbo typecheck` and `npx turbo lint`
3. If there are any linting errors, run `npx turbo lint:fix`
4. To run tests: `npx turbo test --filter @app/<web/api/db>`
5. Never try to start a dev server or curl a local endpoint.
